      "id": "policies",
      "title": "Policies",
      "description": "Students may apply no more than two courses or 8 units from other departments. Approval for outside courses must be petitioned with the undergraduate adviser of the department. Students may apply no more than 4 units of European Languages and Transcultural Studies 195, 197, and 199 as a substitution for one elective course. Each major course must be taken for a letter grade, and students must have an overall grade-point average of 2.0 or better in the major.\n\nStudents who are interested in Danish, Finnish, and Norwegian language instruction may enroll in these courses at other UC campuses through distance learning, and may petition to apply these courses to the major requirements.",
